The article is a press briefing by White House Press Secretary Jay Carney on July 7, 2011. Carney discusses the ongoing negotiations regarding the debt ceiling and deficit reduction. He emphasizes that progress is being made but does not provide specific details. Carney also addresses the topic of Social Security, stating that it is not a factor in the near- and medium-term deficit and that the President is willing to discuss long-term strength of the program. He mentions the importance of a "big deal" in order to achieve significant deficit reduction and states that the President is willing to compromise to reach an agreement. Carney also briefly touches on other topics such as gun control, the situation in South Sudan, and the upcoming anniversary of the Tucson shootings.